        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<a name="34276"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/01/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 13:19:26</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=912"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=912')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=34276&amp;TOPIC_ID=4386&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=AOE+groups+wtf%3F&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I've had very good luck doing aoe groups.  But most necros on my server do not have that luck however.</P><P>We can bring a lot to the table.  My aoe grouping mostly started in droga, pulling goblins for people so we could raise chardok faction.  I got kinda good at it, so they asked me to pull in places like karnors castle basement, HS and a few others.  Just get good at pulling (and surviving) trains and the rest will fall into place.  </P><P>Buff up with manaskin before you pull, and the first mob you agro should be with vexing mordinia, bond of death, whatever.  You might need those hit points later.</P><P>Don't be scared of harmtouches.  You have two invuln spells remember?</P><P>Depending on how many mobs you are planning to pull, you need to actually get in range of mobs in order to sufficiently agro them.  Oftentimes, you will pull mobs just because they are assisting other mobs you agroed.  But these mobs that assist, also forget about you very easily, so try to 'flyby' as many mobs as you can.</P><P>Remember that only 4 mobs (or so) can be in melee range of you at the same time, you have to keep moving.  But you can't move so far from your train or you have mobs that wander off, and come back to bite you later.  (ya know, after your people burned all there mana aoeing the real train you brought)  If you see mobs wandering off, run back in there direction and quickly head back to the group.</P><P>If you want to practice safely, grab a tailor friend (any class with an aoe works fine, even another necro, these mobs have maybe 50 hit points) that needs spiderling silks and hit feerott for a while.  Observe what I mentioned about mobs wandering off you, and get it down on what you need to do to recover your train.  Loot mass quantities of silks, then head to droga with a couple other friends.</P><P>Since they nerfed acrylia and the grey, the places for using aoe groups have become less and less.  Seb is good for it, but it can be very crowded.  HS is nice for it, but you will have to do a lot of moving between wings, which can be challenging for the puller.  Karnors basement is good, just learn those tunnels, gets real confusing sometime.  Katta is also a good place to aoe, but the trick here is finding people that want to destroy there katta faction.  Most good races and the like, prefer to maintain faction here.  I'm sure there are other examples, but those are my personal favorites.</P><P></P><P></P><P><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=107355" target="_blank">Those who have turned away, shall be turned upon. <br> Lich Ravanta Suffer</a>  <img src=icon_smile_evil.gif border=0 align=middle><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

